HEADWORD: Magnetograph
<hw>Mag*net"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Magneto-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An automatic instrument for registering, by
photography or otherwise, the states and variations of any of the
terrestrial magnetic elements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

